<P>
EUREKA QUAKE CAUSED $1.2 MILLION IN DAMAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Staff and wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A preliminary estimate of damage in Eureka's magnitude 5.3 earthquake Monday 
totals $1,208,500, according to officials at the state Office of Emergency 
Services. 
</P>
<P>
 The estimate lists $1,075,000 in damage inside the city of Eureka, including 
46 dwellings that sustained $420,000 in damage, 21 businesses that had $630,000 
in damage and medical facilities with $25,000 in damages. 
</P>
<P>
 In towns and unincorporated areas outside Eureka, damage totaled $133,500 for 
all structures, the agency said. 
</P>
<P>
 Twenty-five minor injuries were reported in the earthquake. 
</P>
