<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: PORT HUENEME; MAN WHO SAID HE HAD GUN ROBS BANK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man who claimed to have a gun robbed a Port Hueneme bank Thursday morning 
and escaped with an undisclosed amount of cash, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The robber handed a note demanding cash to a teller at the Bank of America 
branch in the 700 block of Channel Islands Boulevard at 10:10 a.m., police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police responded to an alarm from the bank, but when officers arrived the man 
had already fled on foot. The robber, described as about 5 feet, 7 inches tall 
and in his 20s, told the teller he had a gun, but it was not seen, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Port Hueneme investigators said they, the FBI and the Oxnard Police Department 
are pursuing several leads. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're very hopeful," Port Hueneme Detective Jerry Beck said. "We've got some 
good leads." MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</TEXT>
