<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; 2 ARRESTED IN THEFT OF WOMAN'S PURSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police have arrested an Oxnard man and a teen-ager on suspicion of snatching 
an 84-year-old woman's purse while she was shopping in Port Hueneme. 
</P>
<P>
 Ali Ostalaza 24, and a 17-year-old Oxnard youth whose name was not released 
because of his age surrounded Beverly Elder of Oxnard outside a store on 
Channel Islands Boulevard Wednesday and grabbed her purse, Port Hueneme police 
said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said the two then ran behind a shopping center. Later that afternoon, 
when a witness spotted the 17-year-old, police were summoned and the youth was 
arrested, police said. Ostalaza later turned himself in at the Oxnard Police 
Department, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The two were booked on suspicion of grand theft, police said. The purse and 
its contents were not recovered. MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
