</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura detectives are investigating an armed robbery at a Motel 6 in which 
two men wearing ski masks stole cash from a clerk and a truck driver 
registering for a room. 
</P>
<P>
 No one was injured in the robbery Wednesday night at the Johnson Drive motel, 
although one of the bandits threatened to kill the driver with a sawed-off 
shotgun while waiting for the clerk to hand over the cash. 
</P>
<P>
 Police would not say how much money was taken. 
</P>
<P>
 Cpl. Jim Burt said the robbery may be linked to a holdup Tuesday night at 
Susie's Deals on Telephone Road. In that incident, two robbers, one carrying a 
sawed-off rifle or shotgun, stole money from a clerk. 
</P>
<P>
 Police have had no suspects in either case, Burt said. JULIE FIELDS 
