</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 20-year-old Camarillo man was arrested on suspicion of attempted burglary 
and of assault with intent to commit rape after threatening a woman from 
outside her front window, Ventura County sheriff's officials said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Thomas Patrick Schmitt is accused of knocking on the window of a 21-year-old 
Camarillo woman about 12:30 a.m. Thursday and threatening to break inside the 
home and assault her, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, who was on the telephone to her sister in Oregon at the time, told 
the sister that Schmitt said he was going to rape her, according to deputies. 
</P>
<P>
 The sister called authorities, and deputies found Schmitt several minutes 
later as he was walking away from the South Glen Drive residence, officials 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Schmitt was held at Ventura County Jail in lieu of $50,000 bail. He is 
scheduled to be arraigned in Ventura County Municipal Court on Tuesday. JEFF 
