<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: PLACENTIA; FREE CHAMBER MUSIC CONCERTS TO BE OFFERED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HOLLY J. WAGNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Placentia Founders Society will host a series of free monthly chamber 
music concerts on Sunday afternoons during the winter and spring. 
</P>
<P>
 The first performance will feature the Fullerton Guitar Quartet, Sean Clegg, 
Stuart Slater, David Adele and Mandeda Uch, and is scheduled for Jan. 15. 
</P>
<P>
 The second, scheduled for Feb. 12, will be given by Trio Sirena, with Kay 
Pech-Anschutz on violin, Manon Robertshaw Trent on cello and Rebecca Rollins on 
piano. 
</P>
<P>
 The Santiago String Quartet, comprising Linda Owen and Carmen Hensley on 
violins, Sue Reineke on viola and Patty Hicks on cello, will perform March 12. 
</P>
<P>
 Rounding out the series will be the Fullerton Symphony Quartet with piano -- 
Etsuo Ejiri and David Lewis on violins, Christine Stilwell on viola, Jordan 
Horwich on cello and Donna Hornick on piano -- in a performance April 23. 
</P>
<P>
 All performances are free, but tax-deductible contributions are welcome. 
Performances are open to the community but seating is limited. All of the 
concerts will be given at 3 p.m. on the stated date at the historic Bradford 
House, 136 Palm Circle. HOLLY J. WAGNER 
</P>
