<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO; DEVELOPER SEEKS CITY APPROVAL FOR 
CONDOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A developer will ask the city early next month to approve construction of 264 
detached condominiums off La Novia Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 The condominiums would complement 22 attatched townhouses under construction 
now as part of a now-scuttled project on 79 1/2 acres. 
</P>
<P>
 A previous developer had permission from the city to build 286 townhouses but 
didn't complete the project, according to C.J. Amstrup, an associate planner 
for the city. 
</P>
<P>
 New city approval for the proposed 264 detatched condominiums is necessary 
because zoning changes are needed to accommodate the project, Amstrup said. 
</P>
<P>
 Amstrup said the city was unsure why the previous developer didn't finish the 
project. The new developer could not be reached Thursday. The developer is 
scheduled to present the project to the city Planning Commission on Jan. 10 and 
to the City Council on Feb. 7.JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
