<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: HUNDREDS EXPECTED TO PRAY FOR PEACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Joining thousands of people throughout the globe, hundreds of Ventura County 
residents are expected to be praying for peace on Earth at 4 a.m. Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 As part of a worldwide effort that began in 1985, people gather at noon 
Greenwich time on the last day of the year and pray for world peace. 
</P>
<P>
 In Camarillo, residents will be served tea, coffee and juice during the 4 a.m. 
prayer at the Center for Positive Living, 221 Daily Drive, Suite 1.  
</P>
<P>
 In Ventura, residents are invited to join members of the Unity Church of 
Ventura County, which will hold a "World Healing Meditation" from 4 to 5 a.m. 
at 2421 Portola Road. 
</P>
<P>
 For those who don't like to get up at dawn, Meditation Mount -- a nonprofit 
meditation center in Ojai -- will hold a prayer for peace at 11:30 p.m. 
Saturday. The center is at the end of Reeves Road. 
</P>
<P>
 Meditation Mount is also inviting residents to a potluck dinner at 8 p.m., 
which will be followed by performances by Brazilian musicians Claudio Vinicius 
and Fernando Corbal. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information call 483-4300 in Camarillo; 646-5508 in Ojai, and 
987-3607 in Ventura. CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</TEXT>
