<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMAN, 74, STABBED 20 TIMES IN HOME; CRIME: A 17-YEAR-OLD NEIGHBOR IS ARRESTED 
IN THE ASSAULT AND APPARENT ROBBERY. THE VICTIM, WHO WAS FOUND HANDCUFFED IN 
HER KITCHEN, IS IN CRITICAL CONDITION. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE TAMAKI and CHIP JOHNSON, TIMES STAFF WRITERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 17-year-old boy was arrested Thursday in the attack and apparent robbery of 
an elderly woman who was stabbed 20 times with a butcher knife and handcuffed 
to a drain pipe in the kitchen of her Reseda home, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Edith Aline Rose, 74, was able to whisper the name of her assailant to 
officers before she underwent surgery for stab wounds in her hands, neck and 
torso, said Detective Rick Swanston of the Los Angeles Police Department.Rose 
was listed in critical condition at a hospital Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
 After hearing his name from Rose, police arrested the teen-ager on suspicion 
of attempted murder, Swanston said. The boy was taken into custody at a Reseda 
fast-food restaurant where he worked. 
</P>
<P>
 "We believe she knew the youth," Swanston said. "They were neighbors." 
</P>
<P>
 Rose has lived alone in a home in the 18200 block of Strathern Street since 
her husband died several years ago, residents said. 
</P>
<P>
 Her alleged assailant lived about a block away in the 8000 block of Wynne 
Avenue, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators estimate that the stabbing occurred early Thursday afternoon. 
Shortly before 3 p.m., a neighbor, concerned because he had not seen Rose all 
day, climbed through an unlocked window and found her semiconscious and 
bleeding. A butcher knife was recovered at the scene. 
</P>
<P>
 Neighborhood residents were shocked by the attack. 
</P>
<P>
 "She is a sweetheart of a gal," said Rick Kahana, 37, another neighbor and 
friend. "I can't imagine anybody would want to hurt her." 
</P>
<P>
 Anthony Federico, who has lived next door to Rose for 32 years, said the woman 
lived a quiet life and worked as a caretaker at the church across the street 
from her home. 
</P>
<P>
 "I don't think she has an enemy in the whole world," said Federico, 69, a 
retired restaurateur. 
</P>
</TEXT>
