<P>
SUIT SAYS DEAF-MUTE WAS ABUSED ON BUS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A deaf and mute Alhambra teen-ager has sued the city's high school district, 
saying she was sexually abused by two male students on a school bus in January. 
</P>
<P>
 The girl, who was 15 when the alleged incidents occurred, said that on Jan. 3, 
4, 5 and 7, the two juveniles threatened to kill her or report her and her 
family to immigration authorities if she did not perform oral sex on one of 
them. 
</P>
<P>
 In her lawsuit, the girl also alleges that on several occasions the boys 
removed articles of her clothing and touched her breasts, buttocks and other 
parts of her body. 
</P>
<P>
 A week after the final incident, according to the lawsuit, the girl and her 
mother complained to officials of Alhambra and its high school district, but no 
action was taken. 
</P>
<P>
 The girl, who communicates with sign language and writing, is still forced to 
ride on the same bus and to attend the same school as the boys, according to 
the lawsuit, which seeks unspecified damages from the boys and their families 
and from Durham Transportation, operator of the bus line, as well as from the 
school district. 
</P>
<P>
 School officials had no immediate comment on the lawsuit. 
</P>
