By MARK I. PINSKY, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An Orange County deputy marshal trying to serve an arrest warrant on an 
assault suspect shot the man at his front door Thursday following a scuffle, 
police said. Tyrone Mathews, 40, was shot in the stomach at 9:30 a.m. at his 
home in the 4800 block of East Maychelle Drive, Police Lt. Vince Howard 
said.Mathews, who was wanted on suspicion of assault with a deadly weapon, was 
in stable condition at Western Medical Center-Santa Ana. 
