<P>
SLAIN MOUNTAIN LION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Re "Slain Mountain Lion Is One That Killed Hiker," Dec. 13: If a person gets 
hit by a car, do we shoot the car? If a person gets killed by a mountain lion, 
why do we kill the mountain lion? 
</P>
<P>
 There are risks associated with all of our activities. We knowingly accept 
these risks when we drive on the roads or go hiking in areas where we know 
there are mountain lions. Should we kill all the mountain lions and other 
wildlife so there are no risks to going hiking in the national forests? 
</P>
<P>
 MARGOT LOWE 
