<P>
LAMP PROJECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I read with enthusiasm your Dec. 21 article about the $106-million grant for 
the LAMP project. That is, I read with enthusiasm until I got to the fourth 
paragraph, where it stated that the money would not be spent on three of the 
four things teachers need most, but would be spent on two things that teachers 
do not need at all.How many of the millions will be spent on administrators 
"gathering data" and "analyzing the progress" while too few teachers continue 
to teach too many students with too few books and too out- of-date equipment in 
too dirty classrooms housed in too broken-down buildings? 
</P>
<P>
 Education needs more money, there is no doubt. But with priorities like these, 
LAMP is just business as usual-bureaucracy first, classroom last. MICHAEL 
HELWIG Canoga Park 
</P>
