<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; WOMAN KILLED IN HIGH-SPEED CAR CRASH; 
ACCIDENTS: POLICE SAY SHE WAS DRIVING OVER 100 M.P.H. WHEN HER VEHICLE STRUCK A 
TREE IN SANTA CLARITA. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK SABBATINI, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Saugus woman died early Thursday after driving away from a party at more 
than 100 m.p.h. and crashing into a tree, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Dayna Hong, 34, was driving her car south on Bouquet Canyon Road when the 
single- car accident occurred about 3:20 a.m. at Alamogordo Road, said Lt. Tim 
Peters of the Santa Clarita Valley Sheriff's Station. 
</P>
<P>
 "We believe she was driving in excess of 100 m.p.h. when she lost control of 
her vehicle," he said. "It came up on two wheels and struck a light, shearing 
off the top of the car, and it ended up hitting a tree." 
</P>
<P>
 The speed limit on Bouquet Canyon Road -- one of the city's main thoroughfares 
-- at the accident site is 50 m.p.h., Deputy Mike Shapiro said. 
</P>
<P>
 Hong died shortly after being transported to Henry Mayo Newhall Memorial 
Hospital in Valencia. 
</P>
<P>
 Sheriff's deputies were called about 2 a.m. to calm a loud party at which Hong 
and her boyfriend were among the guests, Peters said. He said deputies are 
still determining whether she was drinking at the party. 
</P>
<P>
 "Many of the people there were quite under the influence of alcohol," Peters 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
