<HEADLINE>
<P>
OBITUARIES ; ROBERT EMHARDT; ACTOR, SCHOOL BOARD MEMBER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Actor and longtime Ojai school board member Robert Emhardt died this week 
after an extended illness. He was 80. 
</P>
<P>
 An active Ojai resident, Emhardt, originally from Indianapolis, served on the 
Ojai Unified School District Board of Education for about 15 years.He also 
served on the Parks and Recreation Department board, and was well known for his 
performances in local community theater productions. 
</P>
<P>
 Emhardt's love of acting took him to London, where he attended the Royal 
Academy of Dramatic Arts, and then to New York, where he first performed on 
Broadway at age 24. He appeared in 17 Broadway plays and more than 1,000 
television and film productions. 
</P>
<P>
 Emhardt is survived by his wife, Silvia, four children and two grandchildren. 
A memorial service will be held at St. Andrews Episcopal Church in Ojai at 11 
a.m. Jan. 7. 
</P>
</TEXT>
