<P>
LONG BEACH STATE IN SPARTAN FINAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Everett Ratleff came off the bench to score 14 points and Mike Atkinson had 13 
points and eight rebounds as Long Beach State defeated Coppin State, 69-63, 
Thursday in the first round of the Spartan Classic. 
</P>
<P>
 The 49ers (4-1) advance to today's championship game against 15th-ranked 
Michigan State, which defeated Ball State, 117-95. 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach State led, 38-29, at the half, and extended the margin to 12 before 
Coppin State (2-6) put together a 15-4 run. 
</P>
<P>
 The surge, which cut the 49ers' lead to 53-52, was keyed by a pair of 
three-point plays from Stephen Stewart. 
</P>
<P>
 When Stewart made his 13th free throw of the half with 3:10 to play, the score 
was tied, 61-61. 
</P>
<P>
 But the 49ers scored the next seven points to clinch the victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Stewart led all scorers with 22 points, and his 13 free throws tied Shawn 
Respert's two-year-old Spartan Classic record. 
</P>
