<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL / CENTURY TOURNAMENT; SONORA ROLLS PAST CYPRESS INTO FINAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sonora proved why it is one of the best boys' basketball teams in Orange 
County by easily dispatching Cypress, 64-48, in a semifinal of the Century 
Holiday Classic Thursday at Century High. 
</P>
<P>
 Guards Sergio Hernandez, who had 23 points, and Nathan Mirth, who had 13 
points, including three three-pointers, led seventh-ranked Sonora (12-2) over 
10th-ranked Cypress. 
</P>
<P>
 The Raiders, who will play Calvary Chapel in the final tonight, broke open the 
game by outscoring Cypress, 18-5, in the third quarter. Sonora cruised although 
its front line was relatively quiet. 
</P>
<P>
 Seven-foot center Craig Clark, who has signed a letter of intent with San Jose 
State, had 12 points and 10 rebounds but fouled out with 4 minutes 43 seconds 
remaining and Sonora leading, 51-38. Clark took only eight shots and was not 
dominant on offense. 
</P>
<P>
 Starting forwards Chad Fister and Josh Lien combined for only nine points, but 
Sonora didn't need their output to defeat Cypress (11-3) for the second time 
this season. Sonora beat Cypress in the Sonora Cage Classic final, 63-49, on 
Dec. 17. 
</P>
<P>
 "We were sluggish," Sonora Coach Mike Murphy said. "Although Craig fouled out, 
we're confident we can win without him. We're real deep." 
</P>
<P>
 Murphy brought in sophomore Jimmy Landry for Clark in the fourth quarter, and 
Landry scored six of his seven points in the period. 
</P>
<P>
 Although Cypress guard Derek Mitchell scored 22 points, including five 
three-pointers, Clark's presence on defense helped shut down the Centurions' 
inside game. 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress' 6-5 forward Brett Boulton (nine points) and 6-4 forward Chad Boberg 
(five points) made only five of 19 shots. Cypress shot 34% from the field and 
made only one of nine shots in the pivotal third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 In the other semifinal: 
</P>
<P>
 Calvary Chapel 62, Century 51 -- Brandon Wills scored 12 of his 24 points in 
the fourth quarter to help the Eagles (12-2) pull away. Nate Morton scored 12 
points and Kevin Falconer added 11 for Calvary Chapel, which made 16 of 17 free 
throws. 
</P>
<P>
 Hector Beltran scored 13 points and Vibol Ros added 10 for Century (9-5). 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 In consolation games: 
</P>
<P>
 Buena Park 54, Santa Ana 47 -- Ruben Gasso and Towan Oliver each scored 16 
points for Buena Park (7-7). 
</P>
<P>
 Santiago 56, Los Amigos 55 -- Ralph Robledo scored 26 points for Santiago 
(5-7). Kit Ratanaphoulee had 24 points for Los Amigos (5-6). 
</P>
<P>
 Sunny Hills 78, Westminster 41 -- Ben Nicolas was perfect in 11 free-throw 
attempts and scored 21 points for Sunny Hills (6-9). 
</P>
<P>
 Costa Mesa 59, Garden Grove 49 -- Mike Montoya scored 19 points, including six 
three-pointers, for Costa Mesa (6-9). Mike Campuzano had 28 points for Garden 
Grove (5-8). 
</P>
</TEXT>
