<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL / COSTA MESA TOURNAMENT; WOODBRIDGE PLAYERS STAY FRESH, WIN 
TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAN ARRITT, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Woodbridge needed the rest and Coach Eric Bangs knew how to supply it as the 
top-ranked Warriors cruised to a 47-35 victory over Kirkland (Wash.) Lake 
Washington in the championship game of the Costa Mesa girls' basketball 
tournament Thursday night at Costa Mesa High. 
</P>
<P>
 Playing their eighth game in 10 days, Bangs put the Warriors in a zone defense 
and rotated his players regularly enough to keep them productive and prevent 
the Kangaroos from making a threat. 
</P>
<P>
 Woodbridge (13-0) went up, 9-0, on two free throws by Krissy Duperron midway 
through the first quarter and kept Lake Washington in check the rest of the 
game. 
</P>
<P>
 The Warriors took their biggest lead in the third quarter when Erin Stovall 
made one of two free throws for a 35-18 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 However, Woodbridge seemed to run out of gas late in the third quarter after 
Stovall's layup made the score 37-22. 
</P>
<P>
 "We had a lot of tough-luck shots that wouldn't drop," Bangs said. "We were 
stuck on 37 for a while." 
</P>
<P>
 Stovall finally broke the drought when she made two free throws with 4:01 
remaining to give the Warriors a 39-26 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Lake Washington cut the lead to 41-33 on a three-point play by Meghan Geddes, 
but Duperron scored four points down the stretch to halt the comeback. 
</P>
<P>
 Stovall led the Warriors with a game-high 14 points and Duperron scored 11 
despite playing on a sore ankle. 
</P>
<P>
 Angela Burgess was held to six points and was shut out in the second half, but 
the 6-foot-4 center contributed 11 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Sarah Yarborough, who scored 21 in the Kangaroos' semifinal victory over Costa 
Mesa, was held to four second-half points. 
</P>
<P>
 Point guard Kelly Middlesworth led Lake Washington with 10 points and Geddes 
had eight. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 In the third-place game: 
</P>
<P>
 Costa Mesa 54, Huntington Beach 47 -- Center Corri Lurmann's 18 points and 
nine rebounds helped Costa Mesa in the third-place victory. Erin Brown had 12 
points, including two three-pointers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
