<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' SOCCER / OCEAN VIEW HOLIDAY TOURNAMENT; FOUNTAIN VALLEY BEATS OCEAN VIEW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HEATHER STEVENS, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 With four minutes left in the second half Thursday, Ocean View scored the 
tying goal, but Fountain Valley won on penalty kicks after two scoreless 
overtime periods in the final of the Ocean View Holiday girls' soccer 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 But Seahawk Coach Ron Uehle was not disappointed after the 2-2 tie and 3-1 
deficit in penalty kicks. His team had reached the final for the first time in 
the tournament's 13 years. 
</P>
<P>
 Ocean View (9-1-2) dominated the scoreless first half. But Fountain Valley's 
defense, while haphazard, was effective. Goalkeeper Kim Rudloff stopped all 
four Ocean View shots. 
</P>
<P>
 "She's on," Baron Coach Brandee Craig said. "Yesterday Erin (Bottis) played in 
the semifinals, and she was on. They're just switching off." 
</P>
<P>
 Four minutes into the second half, Ocean View's Kimberly Engesser took a 
corner kick. Rudloff seemed to have caught the ball at the near post, then 
dropped it and it rolled across the goal line. 
</P>
<P>
 But the view was different from Fountain Valley's side. "One of our girls 
ducked and as our keeper came out, the ball ricocheted between her and the post 
about three times, then went in," Craig said. 
</P>
<P>
 But sloppy defense nearly did in Ocean View, and Fountain Valley tied the 
score, 1-1, 20 minutes later when fullback Sharon Gillis scored on a free kick 
from about 45 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley (12-1-2) then took the lead with a little more than five 
minutes left in regulation. After a throw-in, Diana Ginns passed to Karrie 
Layton, whose shot was blocked, but Layton got the rebound and passed to Debbie 
Blake, who scored. 
</P>
<P>
 One minute later, Krista Gaeta tapped Engesser's corner kick through a crowd 
and into the net to tie the score at 2. 
</P>
<P>
 After two scoreless overtime periods, Uehle replaced goalkeeper Jacquelyn 
Knebel with Gaeta. 
</P>
<P>
 "Our goalkeeper has never played soccer before, and so she's never been 
through that," Uehle said. He said Knebel's first game was Nov. 15. 
</P>
<P>
 Gaeta had never played in goal either, but Uehle said she had more experience 
in crucial situations. 
</P>
<P>
 Gaeta blocked a shot, then came out of the goal and got Ocean View's only goal 
of the shootout. Cary Groseclose, Maura O'Connell and Mindy Miller scored for 
Fountain Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 In other tournament games: 
</P>
<P>
 Palos Verdes Peninsula 2, El Toro 1 -- Defender Jen Staiti scored the 
Chargers' only goal in the third-place game. Heather Lindstrom had five saves 
and Melody Derloshon three for El Toro (6-5-3). 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei 4, Lakewood Mayfair 3 -- Amy Steiner scored two goals for Mater Dei 
(7-5-2) in the fifth-place game. 
</P>
<P>
 Aliso Niguel 1, Lakewood St. Joseph 1 (Aliso Niguel win on penalty kicks, 3-1) 
-- Cindy Johnson tied the score off Nicole Trott's assist with three minutes 
left in regulation for Aliso Niguel (9-2-1). 
</P>
</TEXT>
