<P>
DESORMEAUX, ALMEIDA SHAKEN IN RACING SPILL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB MIESZERSKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jockeys Kent Desormeaux and Goncalino Almeida escaped serious injury in a 
spill in the first race Thursday at Santa Anita. 
</P>
<P>
 Riding favorite Dancing Generation in the $32,000 claiming race, Desormeaux 
went down when the 3-year-old broke the cannon bone in her right front 
leg.Double Vanilla, behind Dancing Generation and ridden by Almeida, tripped 
over the fallen filly and Almeida was thrown. 
</P>
<P>
 Desormeaux, complaining of a headache, took off his next three mounts, but 
returned to ride in the sixth and seventh races. 
</P>
<P>
 Almeida didn't ride the second race, but returned to win on favored Join The 
Huddle in the fourth. 
</P>
<P>
 On Monday, Fernando Valenzuela suffered a serious back injury in a three-horse 
spill and will be out six to eight weeks. Chris McCarron, who suffered bruised 
ribs in the same spill, was off his mounts again Thursday and is not expected 
to ride today. BOB MIESZERSKI 
</P>
