<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' SOCCER ROUNDUP; MATER DEI TAKES MARINA TITLE IN OVERTIME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MELANIE NEFF 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 With less than one minute remaining in overtime, Mater Dei freshman Greg 
Bechtold took a pass from Kris Hulgreen in front of the net and slammed the 
ball past the Clovis goalkeeper, Aaron Bryan, earning the Monarchs a 2-1 
victory Thursday and a championship in the Marina boys' soccer tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei (8-2-1), last season's Southern Section champion, pressured Bryan 
throughout the overtime period, with junior Ara Akoubian narrowly missing the 
goal wide left earlier in the period, before Bechtold broke free and scored the 
winning goal. 
</P>
<P>
 Both teams moved the ball well and had ample opportunities to score during the 
game, but Mater Dei broke through the Clovis defense first. Freshman Giancarlo 
Barzotti sailed a shot past Bryan with 11 minutes left in regulation, giving 
the Monarchs a 1-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 The Mater Dei defense and senior goalkeeper Paul Gerdis, who gave up only two 
goals in the tournament, held off the Cougars (10-2-1) for most of the game, 
but with less than four minutes remaining in regulation Curt Posey passed the 
ball into Marty Zubiri, who put a header into the right corner of the goal 
beyond Gerdis' reach. MELANIE NEFF 
</P>
</TEXT>
