<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL / THOUSAND OAKS TOURNAMENT; TORRID HART ADVANCES TO TITLE 
GAME, 53-32 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE DESMOND, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Only 10 days ago, the Hart High girls' basketball team was 2-3. 
</P>
<P>
 After Thursday night's 53-32 victory over Cabrillo in a Thousand Oaks 
tournament semifinal, the Indians are 9-3. 
</P>
<P>
 And it wasn't difficult for the Indians to pinpoint the reason for the 
turnaround. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's defense," said Hart Coach Dave Munroe, whose team will meet Chino 
tonight for the championship. 
</P>
<P>
 All-Valley point guard LaCresha Clark credits Munroe with the improvement. 
</P>
<P>
 "He came up with some weird defense," said Clark, who had 18 points and six 
steals. "I didn't even understand it at first, but it seems to be working." 
</P>
<P>
 Indeed. 
</P>
<P>
 Hart led, 11-8, after one quarter, then forced seven Cabrillo turnovers at the 
outset of the second quarter to trigger an 18-0 run and a 29-8 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Center Jaclyn Kuptz contributed 11 points and nine rebounds, while Jamie 
Broneer added nine points. 
</P>
<P>
 The Indians, who staggered early in the season, rebounded to win the 
consolation title in last week's Simi Valley tournament before taking Thousand 
Oaks by storm. 
</P>
<P>
 In three games, they have outscored their tournament opponents, 184-94. 
</P>
<P>
 Chino 42, Thousand Oaks 35 -- Rasheeda Clark scored 15 points to lead Chino 
(9-3) in the other semifinal. 
</P>
<P>
 Teammate Jean Clark added 13 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Nicki LaSala paced Thousand Oaks (7-6) with 12 points, while Jenn Detmer added 
nine points. 
</P>
<P>
 Crescenta Valley 65, Clovis Buchanan 43 -- Freshman Michelle Greco scored 25 
points for Crescenta Valley (11-4) in a consolation semifinal.  
</P>
<P>
 Channel Islands 48, Las Vegas Basic 29 -- Kristina Portillo scored 14 points 
for the Raiders (7-6) in the other consolation semifinal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
