<HEADLINE>
<P>
9 FROM AREA EARN HONORS IN FOOTBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAIGE A. LEECH, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nine regional athletes have been named to the All-Southern Section football 
team, and two area schools each had two representatives. 
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley High defensive linemen Caleb Smith and Chad Shrout garnered 
section honors, and kicker Chris Sailer and linebacker David Dupetit of Notre 
Dame also earned the distinction. 
</P>
<P>
 All are seniors. 
</P>
<P>
 For Dupetit, the Mission League's most valuable player, the awards keep coming 
despite his 5-foot-10, 185-pound frame, much to his surprise. 
</P>
<P>
 "In a way it does (surprise me) because for my position, most guys are a lot 
bigger," Dupetit said. "I'm pretty small for my position. But I guess size 
doesn't matter." 
</P>
<P>
 The section's best offensive players include junior running back Ted Iacenda 
of Hart High, senior receiver Billy Miller of Westlake, and senior linemen Mark 
Manskar of Canyon and Kane Cullum of Crespi. 
</P>
<P>
 Senior punter Ignacio Brache of Village Christian was the only player 
recognized from Division X. Brache averaged 41 yards a punt and kicked 16 field 
goals, including 10 from 40 yards or more and five of 50-plus. 
</P>
<P>
 In three seasons, he had 32 field goals and converted 74 of 78 extra-point 
attempts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
