<HEADLINE>
<P>
ESPERANZA SAFETY HECTOR PLANS TO ATTEND TEXAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB ROHWER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Esperanza safety Anton Hector, a Times All-Orange County first-team selection, 
said Thursday he has made an oral commitment to play football at Texas. 
</P>
<P>
 The 6-foot-1, 172-pound Hector had six interceptions last season and was an 
All-Sunset League selection. 
</P>
<P>
 Hector, who will major in business, said he chose Texas because "it's a good 
program and they showed the most interest from the start." 
</P>
<P>
 Hector is also a standout hurdler and sprinter on the Esperanza track and 
field team. He is the cousin of former Texas A&M and New York Jet running back 
Johnny Hector. BOB ROHWER 
</P>
