<TEXT>
<P>
 The Alemany High girls' basketball team turned in a performance Thursday that 
Coach Melissa Hearlihy called, "the best game we've played in a long time," to 
advance to the finals of the Surf 'N Slam tournament in La Jolla. 
</P>
<P>
 "We haven't played that well since the fourth playoff game last year," said 
Hearlihy of her team's 72-45 victory over New Jersey Red Bank. 
</P>
<P>
 Paced by Kathy Reith's eight points, the Indians (9-1) used a 21-4 run in the 
second quarter to extend their lead, 39-21. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 In other girls' games: 
</P>
<P>
 Buena 58, St. Patrick's (Canada) 36 -- Nicole Greathouse had 10 points and 16 
rebounds as Buena (3-2) advanced to the consolation final of the La Jolla 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 El Camino Real 56, Grant 47 -- Junior guard Tami Jones scored 25 points, had 
10 assists and grabbed 10 rebounds to lead the Conquistadores (4-6) to 
fifth-place in the Birmingham tournament. It was her second career 
triple-double. BOYS' 
</P>
