announced in September, would eliminate competition between Glendale-based 
Nestle and Alpo PetFoods of Allentown, Pa., a subsidiary of Grand Metropolitan 
Inc. The sale may also have raised the odds for collusion among the remaining 
cat food companies, the FTC said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
