<HEADLINE>
<P>
OC HIGH / STUDENT NEWS AND VIEWS; INLINE; STANDING FIRM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Capistrano Unified School District has gone on record against music and 
videotapes or computer games that depict or promote the killing of human 
beings, celebrate violence or desensitize children to the value of human life. 
</P>
<P>
 "There is an emerging body of evidence that indicates that there are links 
that exist between increased use by children of computerized games which 
simulate killing" and a lack of respect for human life, the district said in a 
written statement. 
</P>
<P>
 "The additional negative influence of music and related videotapes that 
promote violence or celebrate killing adds to an unhealthy environment which 
may lead children to accept violence as a common fact of life in society." 
</P>
