<HEADLINE>
<P>
BEEN THERE, DONE THAT; PSYCHOBABBLE IS DEAD. SO IS YOUR INNER CHILD, SO YOU CAN 
STOP LISTENING NOW. WHINING IS DEFINITELY OUT, AS IS STRENUOUS EXERCISE -- 
BETTER TO RELAX AND ENJOY A NICE BOOK ABOUT THE GOOD OLD DAYS, A FAVORITE 
CD-ROM DISC OR SEX! DITCH ALL THOSE PLAID SHIRTS AND COMBAT BOOTS FROM '94 AND 
SLIP BACK INTO SOMETHING SATIN. BETTER YET, COOK UP SOME SPAM. IT'S ALMOST 1995 
AND EVERYTHING OLD IS NEW AGAIN. . . .; FASHION / ROSE-MARIE TURK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROSE-MARIE TURK, Rose-Marie Turk is a Life & Style fashion writer. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 This is the year of revenge -- for the woman who never liked plaid shirts, 
combat boots, backpacks or tattoos. For the woman who never gave up on shoulder 
pads, gloves, hats, high heels -- or her waistline.For the woman who 
pooh-poohed her inner child and pampered her inner lady. 
</P>
<P>
 Glamour, sweetie-darlings, is big again. Think '40s and '50s sexy. Start with 
a suit or dress -- the tiny waist encircled with a thin-thin belt (the year's 
must-have accessory), a fanny emphasizing tight skirt (down to the calves to 
produce a wiggle-walk), hat-with-something (veil, cherries, flowers), spike 
heels and a snappy little hand-held bag. 
</P>
<P>
 Bias-cut dresses and shiny fabrics are part of the glam-track. Hair will shine 
too. (Think Breck girls.)  
</P>
<P>
 The bare midriff remains. And so do bare thighs, because in '90s freewheeling 
style, the mini will not die. Nor will visible corsets, bras and bustiers. But 
there is a newcomer: decorative panties. 
</P>
<P>
 Today's glamour puss is a dash of every goddess from Veronica Lake to 
model-of-the-moment Nadja Auermann. The rules for shopping? Recall them all, 
think feline-to-the-max, then be your own woman. 
</P>
<P>
 And get ready to find a Hollywood-retro sort of guy or a fashion gangster.  
</P>
<P>
 Yes, sweetie-darlings, memories of Cary Grant and Al Capone have invaded 
menswear. The Armani man, however, remains as strong as ever, which means any 
sartorial sage worth his salt will have a wardrobe mix of Italian mod, old 
movie and the mob. 
</P>
</TEXT>
