 Best news: L.A. airport commissioners voted not to renew Host Marriott's 
contract after 34 years. 
</P>
<P>
 Most anticipated opening: Eclipse. 
</P>
<P>
 The longest goodby: Nicky Blair's five-month farewell. 
</P>
<P>
 Fastest backpedal: "L.A.'s EKG registers flat" (French consul-general 
Jean-Maurice Ripert insists he was misquoted in the French magazine Figaro 
Madame when talking about life in Los Angeles). 
</P>
<P>
 Souvenir menus, anyone?: Dive! $5, Country Star $15 (but it lights up). 
</P>
<P>
 Most flops: BG's short-order souffles. 
</P>
<P>
 Windfall PR: Mezzaluna in Brentwood. 
</P>
<P>
 Dumbest move: Morton's from one side of Robertson to the other. 
</P>
