<DATE>
<P>
December 30, 1994, Friday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 13; Column 1; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
532 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; NOWLING'S SHOT GETS TITANS PAST PEPPERDINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tara Nowling's jumper from the free-throw line with seven seconds remaining 
gave Cal State Fullerton a 61-59 victory over Pepperdine in a nonconference 
women's basketball game Thursday in Malibu. 
</P>
<P>
 Pepperdine (4-3), which rallied after trailing by nine points at halftime, 
missed a shot at the buzzer.Koko Lahanas had 18 points and 11 rebounds and 
Shayla Bradshaw scored 18 points for the Titans (3-4). 
</P>
<P>
 Lisa Siders had 20 points and 11 rebounds and former Huntington Beach High 
player Clare Walker scored 13 for Pepperdine. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Utah State men's tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Lewis-Clark State 88, Chapman 72 -- Lonnie Perteet scored 31 points and James 
Stoner had 17 to lead Lewis-Clark State (8-6). Ramin Bastani led Chapman (6-4) 
with 23 points. A 25-11 run early in the game proved costly for the Panthers. 
</P>
<P>
 In the UC San Diego women's tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Millikan (Ill.) 63, Chapman 56 -- Melody Earle scored a game-high 20 points 
for Chapman (5-4), which fell in a semifinal. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference women's basketball: 
</P>
<P>
 Southern California College 76, Bethel (Kan.) 68 -- The Vanguards (3-5) broke 
a four-game losing streak by rallying from a 38-29 first-half deficit. 
</P>
<P>
 Heather Brannan made three of four three-point shots in the second half and 
finished with 15 points and eight assists. Tina Southard scored 18 for SCC. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story; JC Sports 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
